! Just before the exit, we need to call vms_shell_execve instead of
! shell_execve.  We apparently need the additional async parameter.
! old sequence:
! * call vms_shell_execve()
! * dispose_word_array (args)  - Done internal to vms_shell_execve?
! * vmsutil_restore_std_fds()
! * if pid == special VMS pid, then free (command) return - Not needed!
! * Otherwise, goto parent_return that does a free (command) return.
! * Note that the args[] array is dynamically allocated so must be
!   freed before exit.
! The contents of the args[] array should not be freed.
VMS_INSERT_BEFORE('exit (shell_execve', '#ifdef __VMS');
